<div id="review_709672693" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/709672693" />
    <a title="Rob Baker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18084923-rob-baker"><img alt="Rob Baker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1382749423p2/18084923.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/709672693?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rob Baker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rob Baker" href="/user/show/18084923-rob-baker">Rob Baker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18084923-rob-baker?shelf=nonfiction-independent-reading">nonfiction-independent-reading</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer709672693" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer936862919606481234">&quot;Learn to look at other beings with the eyes of compassion.&quot; Hanh&apos;s meditations (it&apos;s actually, according to the introduction, a series of talks he gave) include many such helpful ideas about how to integrate peace and awareness into one&apos;s life. Meditation, he reminds us, is not about withdrawing from the world but about bringing one&apos;s most reflective and present self into the world.<br/><br/>The Buddhist monk method of dealing with interpersonal conflicts that he outlines in the chapter titled &quot;Interbein</span>
  <span id="freeText936862919606481234" style="display:none">"Learn to look at other beings with the eyes of compassion." Hanh's meditations (it's actually, according to the introduction, a series of talks he gave) include many such helpful ideas about how to integrate peace and awareness into one's life. Meditation, he reminds us, is not about withdrawing from the world but about bringing one's most reflective and present self into the world.<br /><br />The Buddhist monk method of dealing with interpersonal conflicts that he outlines in the chapter titled "Interbeing" is one that could be used beneficially by all. I especially like the step called "Covering Mud with Straw" in which the two arguing monks first have to compliment one another, and then say something about how they themselves were wrong. It's a seven-step process that seems worth trying out. <br /><br />Because it's a series of lectures, it's a bit scattershot in terms of the topics it covers, and often it just touches on things, not really going into much detail, perhaps assuming the reader/listener has prior knowledge about things. For this reason, it is not the ideal book for someone just beginning to read about meditation, but there are enough insightful and helpful gems scattered throughout to make it useful reading for all</span>
  <a data-text-id="936862919606481234" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


