<span id="freeTextContainer14031042534199770350">I recommend it on my top-ten list of Peace resources. In order to achieve peace, we must be peace. This simple truth is the theme of this inspiring collection of lectures, given by Buddhist monk, scholar, poet and peace activist Thich Nhat Hanh. If we are to change the world, he explains, we need to begin with ourselves, and awaken that eternal part of us where true peace resides - our own Buddha nature. <br/><br/>His straight forward writing style helps a person to realise how easy this awakening can act</span>
  <span id="freeText14031042534199770350" style="display:none">I recommend it on my top-ten list of Peace resources. In order to achieve peace, we must be peace. This simple truth is the theme of this inspiring collection of lectures, given by Buddhist monk, scholar, poet and peace activist Thich Nhat Hanh. If we are to change the world, he explains, we need to begin with ourselves, and awaken that eternal part of us where true peace resides - our own Buddha nature. <br /><br />His straight forward writing style helps a person to realise how easy this awakening can actually be. He explains that with inner peace as the guide and criterion for all of our actions, we transform our way of living into one genuinely capable of bringing lasting peace into a troubled world. <br /><br />The book also helps us with some basic understanding of Buddhism and meditation. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14031042534199770350" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

